
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `deallocvt` baraye azad kardane (deallocate) yek virtual terminal (VT) estefade mishavad. Vaghti ke VT digar estefade nemishavad, ba in dastoor mishe an ra az memory hazf kard ta resource-ha azad shavand.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `deallocvt N` --> 🔢 `N` shomare terminal virtuali ast ke mikhaid azad konid. Agar shomare dade nashavad, terminal jari azad mishavad.
    🔹 `deallocvt -k N` --> 🔪 VT ra be force mikoshe (kill) va azad mikonad, hata agar kasio dar an terminal logg-in bashad. Ehtiat konid!

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ deallocvt 2

    🔹 Terminal virtual shomare 2 ra azad mikonad.

    $ deallocvt -k 3

    🔹 Terminal virtual shomare 3 ra majbur mikonad bebandad va azad mikonad.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ deallocvt
    
    🔹 Terminal virtual jari (current) ra azad mikonad, agar hich terminal digari be an vasl nabashad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `deallocvt` command is used to deallocate a virtual terminal (VT).  When a VT is no longer in use, this command can free up memory and resources associated with it.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `deallocvt N` --> 🔢 `N` is the number of the virtual terminal you want to deallocate. If no number is given, the current terminal is deallocated.
    🔹 `deallocvt -k N` --> 🔪 Forcefully kill and deallocate VT `N`, even if someone is logged in. Use with caution!

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ deallocvt 2

    🔹 Deallocates virtual terminal number 2.

    $ deallocvt -k 3

    🔹 Forces virtual terminal number 3 to close and deallocate.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ deallocvt
    
    🔹 Deallocates the current virtual terminal, if no other terminal is attached to it.
